    "reasoning": "The module TopModule implements a finite state machine (FSM) to search for message boundaries based on the PS/2 protocol. The FSM starts in an initial state where it waits for a byte with in[3] == 1. Once found, it proceeds to collect two more bytes, then asserts 'done' on the third byte. The states are: IDLE (waiting for first byte), COLLECT (collecting two remaining bytes), and DONE (assert 'done'). Reset initializes the state to IDLE. Counters track the received bytes. The FSM transitions between states on each clock. Outputs done is high only in DONE state. No explicit reset in some state registers for efficiency, using initial blocks for known values. Combinational logic uses always @(*) with no explicit sensitivity list. Ensured no 'inside' or 'unique' keywords.",
    "module": "module TopModule (clk, reset, in, done);\n    input logic clk;\n    input logic reset;\n    input logic [7:0] in;\n    output logic done;\n\n    // States\n    localparam IDLE = 2'b00;\n    localparam COLLECT = 2'b01;\n    localparam DONE_STATE = 2'b10;\n\n    reg [1:0] state = IDLE;\n    reg [1:0] next_state;\n    reg [1:0] byte_count = 0;\n    reg [1:0] next_byte_count;\n\n    // State transition\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            IDLE: begin\n                next_state = (in[3]) ? COLLECT : IDLE;\n                next_byte_count = 1;\n            end\n            COLLECT: begin\n                if (byte_count == 2) begin\n                    next_state = DONE_STATE;\n                    next_byte_count = 0;\n                end else begin\n                    next_state = COLLECT;\n                    next_byte_count = byte_count + 1;\n                end\n            end\n            DONE_STATE: begin\n                next_state = IDLE;\n                next_byte_count = 0;\n            end\n            default: begin\n                next_state = IDLE;\n                next_byte_count = 0;\n            end\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Update state and counters\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset) begin\n            state <= IDLE;\n            byte_count <= 0;\n        end else begin\n            state <= next_state;\n            byte_count <= next_byte_count;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Output logic\n    assign done = (state == DONE_STATE);\nendmodule"
}
